    "Stokes data is given by the notion of Stokes local systems [BY15, Boa21], which we now recall.",
    "In our case with Σ = P 1, given an irregular class Θ at ∞, the idea is to define a slightly modified surface by introducing a puncture near each singular direction in the real blow-up Σ of the Riemann sphere at ∞.",
    "A Stokes local system is then a local system on this new surface which near ∂ is I-graded (with irregular class Θ) and such that the monodromies around the new, so-called tangential punctures are elements in the corresponding Stokes groups.",
    "More precisely, we define the new surface Σ(Θ) as follows.",
    "We define the halo H ⊂ Σ as a tubular neighbourhood of ∂."
  ],
